HEADWORD: Mugiloidea
<hw>Mugiloidea</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A suborder of fishes
distinguished by abdominal pelvic fins, including the families
<fam>Mugilidae</fam>; <fam>Atherinidae</fam>; and
<fam>Sphyraenidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> suborder <subord>Mugiloidea</subord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

